Defendant in custody.   
Count 1 - Battery to law enforcement officer - Guilty plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2, 3, and 4.   Motion granted.   Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.   Conditions of probation are:
1) Six (6) months jail, imposed and stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion; 
2) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
4) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
5) AODA assessment and follow through; 
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge.   
Minutes.
